<section id="Deleting_a_Policy" remap="TID_14734">
	<title>Deleting a Policy</title>
	<para>
		You can remove policies that you no longer need. You can only remove policies that are not assigned to a policy profile.
	</para>
	<procedure>
		<title>To Delete a Policy</title>
		<step>
			<para>
				Navigate to <menuchoice><guimenu>Control</guimenu><guisubmenu>Explorer</guisubmenu></menuchoice>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click the <guimenuitem>Policies</guimenuitem> accordion, and select the policy you want to remove.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1847.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> (<guilabel>Configuration</guilabel>), 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1861.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> (<guilabel>Delete this Host/VM and Instance Policy</guilabel>).
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guibutton>OK</guibutton> to confirm.
			</para>
		</step>
	</procedure>
</section>